The paper deals with the security and communication challenges in vehicular networks, which are typically addressed in the computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The proposed solution involves the use of blockchain and elliptic curve cryptography, which are also relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the scalability and lightweight nature of the proposed scheme, which are aspects of software engineering (cs.SE).
